"restrictions","to","insure","congenial","neighbors",".","A","completely","planned","globular","settlement","in","a","near","arm","of","our","own","galaxy",".","Low","taxes","and","liberal","credit",".","Financing","our","specialty","--","''","\n","\n","``","And","you","had","better","have","an","armed","escort","when","you","return",",","''","said","Father","Briton",".","\n","\n","``","Why","in","cosmos","would","we","want","an","armed","escort","?","''","\n","\n","``","It","'s","as","phony","as","a","seven-credit","note","!","''","\n","\n","``","You",",","a","man","of","the","cloth","doubt","it","?","And","us","ready","skeptics","convinced","by","our","senses","?","Why","do","you","doubt","?","''","\n","\n","``","It","is","only","the","unbelieving","who","believe","so","easily","in","obvious","frauds",".","Theologically","unsound",",","dramaturgically","weak",",","philologically","impossible",",","zoologically","rigged",",","salted","conspicuously","with","gold","and","shot","through","with","anachronisms",".","And","moreover","he","was","afraid","to","play","me","at","checkers",".","''","\n","\n","``","What","?","''","\n","\n","``","If","I","have","a","preternatural","intellect","I","would","n't","be","afraid","of","a","game","of","checkers","with","anyone",".","Yet","there","was","an","unusual","mind","there","somewhere",";","it","was","just","that","he","chose","not","to","make","our","acquaintance","personally",".","''","\n","\n","``","They","looked","at","the","priest","thoughtfully",".","\n","\n","``","But","it","was","Paradise","in","one","way",",","''","said","Steiner","at","last",".","\n","\n","``","How","?","''","\n","\n","``","All","the","time","we","were","there","the","woman","did","not","speak",".","''"]}},"question":"What ultimately makes the priest disbelieve what they've seen, despite his faith?","answers":["Someone like Adam would not be afraid of playing checkers, or being personable. ","The illusion is too perfect, and it feels inauthentic to him. "],"correctAnswerIndex":0,"roles":{"Debater A":"Bubbles Brandywine","Debater B":"Quibble Quackenbush"},"offlineJudges":{"Nibbles Nuggetson":"timed"},"creationTime":1680206043370},"rounds":[{"SimultaneousSpeeches":{"speeches":{"0":{"speaker":"Bubbles Brandywine","timestamp":1682974747443,"content":[{"Text":{"text":"Context: the priest is a member of a survey team who land on a moon which appears to be the biblical garden of paradise. In reality, it is a ruse designed to lure them back so their ships can be raided. However, the priest catches on to the true nature of the place.\n\nThe priest takes numerous issues with the illusion, so it's clearly not the case that it's \"too perfect\". In addition to these faults, the priest notes that \"Adam\" "}},{"Quote":{"span":[4281,4290]}},{"Text":{"text":". This is odd because \"Adam\" is presents himself as being extremely intelligent. As the priest then says: "}},{"Quote":{"span":[4299,4317]}},{"Text":{"text":"."}}]},"1":{"speaker":"Quibble Quackenbush","timestamp":1680554625712,"content":[{"Text":{"text":"A group of explorers comes across a planet that appears to be an unspoiled Garden of Eden with Adam/Eve, evil serpent, etc. The members of the group are fooled, except the priest, because it seems very inauthentic: "}},{"Quote":{"span":[4256,4277]}},{"Text":{"text":". The priest does mention checkers, but it's just one element of the reasoning, where most of his disbelief comes from the perfect inauthenticity of the illusion. \n\nImportantly, there is nothing in the story about personability. A needs to show that Adam in the story was afraid of being personable. There is no evidence to support this (in fact, Adam is extremely personable)"}}]}}}},{"SequentialSpeeches":{"speeches":{"0":{"speaker":"Bubbles Brandywine","timestamp":1682975150902,"content":[{"Text":{"text":"B cites the exact sentence which continues into my initial quote. Judge, does that sound like \"perfection\"? The priest is fully aware of the shoddy design and artifice of the moon, so it's clear that he doesn't think it's \"too perfect\". \n\nAdam's lack of \"personable-ness\" can be seen in the way he evades answering questions in a normal sense (remember, he is trying to deceive them!): Priest: "}},{"Quote":{"span":[2687,2698]}},{"Text":{"text":" Adam: "}},{"Quote":{"span":[2702,2711]}},{"Text":{"text":" And also from the fact that he refuses to play checkers!\n\nB says that this is \"just one element of reasoning\". In the priests on words: "}},{"Quote":{"span":[2939,2962]}}]},"1":{"speaker":"Quibble Quackenbush","timestamp":1682975953387,"content":[{"Text":{"text":"A is lying about that last quote, taking it completely out of context. The \"question\" being referred to is not about whether the garden is an illusion - it's just about Adam's intellect:\nAdam: "}},{"Quote":{"span":[2888,2898]}},{"Text":{"text":" (other guy): "}},{"Quote":{"span":[2910,2928]}},{"Text":{"text":". A is trying to connect that quote to the question of whether it's an illusion, but it comes from a totally separate part of the passage and is unrelated.\n\nThere will always be a paradox in disbelieving something because it's too believable - what matters is that the world is very convincing, and that the priest disbelieves in it. "}},{"Quote":{"span":[3444,3455]}},{"Quote":{"span":[3464,3470]}}]}}}},{"SequentialSpeeches":{"speeches":{"0":{"speaker":"Bubbles Brandywine","timestamp":1683302448045,"content":[{"Text":{"text":"The question of Adam's intelligence is _part of the ruse_. But moreover, no, I'm not lying, B is. The members of the crew turn to the priest to figure out of this really is eden because he is most knowledgable on matters of religion. See their numerous questions about reality/religious: \n- "}},{"Quote":{"span":[2293,2314]}},{"Text":{"text":"\n- "}},{"Quote":{"span":[2547,2573]}},{"Text":{"text":"\nHappy to cite more in future rounds. The entire purpose of these questions is to interrogate what the crew sees. It's not \"unrelated\" at all.\n\nAlso: B is BLATANTLY lying about who said their quote: "}},{"Quote":{"span":[3457,3467]}}]},"1":{"speaker":"Quibble Quackenbush","timestamp":1683322241655,"content":[{"Text":{"text":"How am I lying about my last quote - I never said the priest said it?? I was using that as evidence that *the world is convincing* - of course the priest wouldn't say that, because he doesn't believe the ruse! I couldn't include the rest of the line b/c of the quote/length limits.\n\nThe point is just that the illusion is very well-done - too well done in fact for the priest to believe it. \n\nFinally: B's quotes about \"personability\" are very weak (cf. 2687) - there isn't any evidence that Adam isn't personable - he just answers the question!"}}]}}}},{"NegotiateEnd":{"votes":{"0":true,"1":true}}},{"OfflineJudgments":{"judgments":{"Nibbles Nuggetson":{"mode":"stepped","startTimeMillis":1683904505533,"judgments":[{"distribution":[0.5,0.5],"feedback":{"speaker":"Nibbles Nuggetson","timestamp":1683904508204,"content":[]},"endDebate":false},{"distribution":[0.7,0.3000000000000001],"feedback":{"speaker":"Nibbles Nuggetson","timestamp":1683904554845,"content":[]},"endDebate":false},{"distribution":[0.8,0.19999999999999998],"feedback":{"speaker":"Nibbles Nuggetson","timestamp":1683904656692,"content":[]},"endDebate":false},{"distribution":[0.99,0.010000000000000007],"feedback":{"speaker":"Nibbles Nuggetson","timestamp":1683904793885,"content":[]},"endDebate":true}]}}}}],"feedback":{"Bubbles Brandywine":{"Debater":{"answers":{"subjective correctness":4,"clarity":{"first":3,"second":3},"factual accuracy":{"first":4,"second":1},"evidence use":{"first":4,"second":4},"evidence in story":{"first":4,"second":2},"facts versus semantics":{"first":1,"second":2},"clash":{"first":4,"second":4}}}},"Nibbles Nuggetson":{"OfflineJudge":{"answers":{"factual informativeness (comparative)":{"first":3,"second":3},"evidence in debate":{"first":4,"second":1},"clarity":{"first":4,"second":4